OL,3,CFears wage rises will increase prices
OL,4,Cfor customers
OL,6,FNearly 200,000 people here are due to
OL,7,Fget a pay rise, as changes to the
OL,8,Fminimum and living wage come into
OL,9,Feffect on Tuesday.
OL,11,FHowever, there is a warning from
OL,12,Fbusinesses that the changes - along
OL,13,Fwith increases to the amount of
OL,14,Fnational insurance which companies
OL,15,Fwill have to pay - may result in price
OL,16,Frises for consumers.
OL,18,FRetailer Peter McBride employs more
OL,19,Fthan 500 staff across 16 shops, the
OL,20,Fincrease in costs mean his wage bill
OL,21,Fwill go up by 10%.
